gomodel:SYNGO_1004  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Using heterologous expression systems (HEK293 or COS cells) in combination with primary cultures of retina ganglia cells, the authors show that hevin bridges NRX1alpha and NL1B (Fig. 4). Fig. 5 shows using respective mouse mutants that hevin indeed is required for thalamocortical synapse formation.. Experimental description: \" Excitatory synaptic circuitry within the mouse V1 cortex\". Figure legend Fig. 5, p. 190\n\n5/9/2017 Pim\n- The species of the over-expressed hevin is not mentioned in the paper." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" ;
        dc:date           "2017-09-05" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1004" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

